The paper deals with algorithmic applications of Carath\'{e}odory's theorem in the context of computing Nash equilibria and dense subgraphs. This makes it likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT), Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves approximation algorithms, which could place it in the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories.
